-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mkm1665702764922.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mkm1665702764922.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mkm1665702764922.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mkm1665702764922\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n What's New in MSS U5.2\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"mkm1665702764922__what_s_new_in_mss_u_154511\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The MSS U5.2 connector enables you to connect to Microsoft SQL Server 2017.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mkm1665702764922__topic_d33907e1_d33908e1_d33909e1_d33910e1_d33911e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1089012e48\">Default behavior of\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql92npw</span> has changed </h2>When using MSS U5.2, the sql92npw\n         option defaults to on. In earlier versions of the connector the default was off. For more\n         information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"spv1665702730389.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/spv1665702730389.html\" title=\"Determines how NULL values are handled in concatenation and aggregate functions.\">sql92npw</a>.</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529959\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529959\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "What's New in MSS U5.2 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 What's New in MSS U5.2 The MSS U5.2 connector enables you to connect to Microsoft SQL Server 2017. Default behavior of sql92npw has changed When using MSS U5.2, the sql92npw option defaults to on. In earlier versions of the connector the default was off. For more information, see sql92npw . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}